{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"037ccff9-bd20-4eba-8350-dfe5621907bc","content":"No repo files found, so here's general guidance for your Azure Pipelines migration:\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform doesn't use `vstest.console.exe`, so `VSTest@3` won't work. Use a `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain `script`) instead:\n\n```yaml\n# Before (VSTest@3)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform via dotnet test)\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **TRX reports** — pass `--logger \"trx\"` to keep generating `.trx` files.\n2. **Code coverage** — use `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (or `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` for Coverlet).\n3. **Publish results** — add a `PublishTestResults@2` task since `DotNetCoreCLI@2` doesn't auto-publish when using the new platform:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n```\n\n4. **Publish coverage** — if using the Microsoft collector:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### In your test projects\n\nMake sure each test `.csproj` opts in:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis enables the built-in MSTest runner (Microsoft.Testing.Platform) so `dotnet test` uses it instead of VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a028870-ae20-4446-9903-2606167bc07d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":661,"requestId":"082C:1DCDBF:7D37EC0:8B7667F:69EABEC3"},"id":"7df99099-646c-4854-99c3-c934308adbff","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:52:31.972Z","parentId":"d4e79bc2-6f68-4ce2-a578-614a0b46ef65"}
